buntu/+source/php5/+bug/1594041","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eA quick status update on this. The underlying PHP vulnerability has been assigned \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.openwall.com%2Flists%2Foss-security%2F2016%2F06%2F21%2F3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCVE-2015-8935 by MITRE\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and the bug to Ubuntu is tracked at \u003ca title=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/php5/+bug/1594041\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fbugs.launchpad.net%2Fubuntu%2F%2Bsource%2Fphp5%2F%2Bbug%2F1594041\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/php5/+bug/1594041\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-06-21T12:34:16.998Z","updated_at":"2016-06-21T12:34:16.998Z","actor":{"username":"lukasreschke","cleared":false,"url":"/lukasreschke","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/037/891/e7fea4d5383dc07d1fe767b02f3bda2bc7639c63_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"nextcloud","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1047429,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"A short update on this one, our current consideration is to not do any special patches in our code base for this situation. The impact seems rather low and we'd like to avoid adding special patches for this situation to the code. \n\nWe do believe that it's better if distributions do backport this PHP security patch. \n\nOn the affected distributions, we have the following information:\n- Ubuntu 12.04 / 14.04: The security issue has been acknowledged and rated as \"Medium\". (https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/php5/+bug/1594041)\n- Redhat / CentOS: The security issue has been acknowledged and rated as \"Moderate\", the versions in the Red Hat Software Collections are already secure. (https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1348927)\n\nAs to our current knowledge other major distribution vendors are not affected. Debian for example ships recent PHP versions including a patch for this issue.\n\nI'll check back internally on how we want to handle this issue. I'll get back to you in a bit! Thanks again!","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eA short update on this one, our current consideration is to not do any special patches in our code base for this situation. The impact seems rather low and we\u0026#39;d like to avoid adding special patches for this situation to the code. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe do believe that it\u0026#39;s better if distributions do backport this PHP security patch. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the affected distributions, we have the following information:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUbuntu 12.04 / 14.04: The security issue has been acknowledged and rated as \u0026quot;Medium\u0026quot;. (\u003ca title=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/php5/+bug/1594041\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fbugs.launchpad.net%2Fubuntu%2F%2Bsource%2Fphp5%2F%2Bbug%2F1594041\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/php5/+bug/1594041\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRedhat / CentOS: The security issue has been acknowledged and rated as \u0026quot;Moderate\u0026quot;, the versions in the Red Hat Software Collections are already secure. (\u003ca title=\"https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1348927\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fbugzilla.redhat.com%2Fshow_bug.cgi%3Fid%3D1348927\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1348927\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs to our current knowledge other major distribution vendors are not affected. Debian for example ships recent PHP versions including a patch for this issue.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;ll check back internally on how we want to handle this issue. I\u0026#39;ll get back to you in a bit! Thanks again!\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-06-30T13:52:10.565Z","updated_at":"2016-06-30T13:58:19.843Z","actor":{"username":"lukasreschke","cleared":false,"url":"/lukasreschke","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/037/891/e7fea4d5383dc07d1fe767b02f3bda2bc7639c63_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"nextcloud","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1047521,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Thanks for the update! No worries! :)","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eThanks for the update! No worries! :)\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-06-30T14:47:39.026Z","updated_at":"2016-06-30T14:47:39.026Z","actor":{"username":"fransrosen","cleared":true,"url":"/fransrosen","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/001/634/6569f1cff6ac26c01a91db469d8707228965f09f_original.jpg/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"nextcloud","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1111025,"is_internal":false